<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 12:08PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Comanche, southern Grady and southeastern Caddo Counties through 1245
PM CDT...
At 1207 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sterling, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Elgin, Rush Springs, Fletcher, Sterling, Alex, Agawam, Ninnekah and
Acme.
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 54 and 74.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
